 {"id":"bd-242","title":"Update import.go to use CreateIssues for bulk imports","description":"Modify cmd/bd/import.go to use CreateIssues instead of CreateIssue loop.

After bd-224, import already normalizes closed_at, so this is straightforward:
1. Normalize all issues in batch (closed_at handling)
2. Call CreateIssues once with full batch
3. Much simpler than current loop","design":"```go
// After normalizing all issues
for _, issue := range issues {
    if issue.Status == types.StatusClosed {
        if issue.ClosedAt == nil {
            now := time.Now()
            issue.ClosedAt = &now
        }
    } else {
        issue.ClosedAt = nil
    }
}

// Single batch call (5-15x faster!)
return store.CreateIssues(ctx, issues, "import")
